menu "Async / Coroutines"

config ASYNC
    bool "Enable stackless coroutine (async/await) support"
    default y
    help
      Provides ASYNC_BEGIN / ASYNC_END / ASYNC_YIELD / ASYNC_AWAIT /
      ASYNC_AWAIT_CORO macros for writing stackless cooperative coroutines
      in C.

      Each coroutine is a plain C function that stores its resume point in
      a small async_t struct — no extra stack is required.  Persistent state
      must live in a caller-supplied context struct.

      Required by the job scheduler (CONFIG_JOB_SCHEDULER).  Can also be
      used directly in application code without the scheduler.

endmenu
